emics. In addition to that, the presented modelling study provides a\ngood framework for the creation of subexponential-growth-models for assessing\nthe spread of COVID-19.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 11 May 2020 16:42:03 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-05-12"}
