 GCs\nformed in-situ from those formed ex-situ. These results suggest a simple\npicture of GC formation, in which GCs are a natural outcome of normal star\nformation in the typical, gas-rich galaxies that are the progenitors of\npresent-day galaxies.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 11 May 2020 18:00:04 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-06-03"}
