{"id":"2005.05492","submitter":"Arnaldo Mandel","authors":"Mikhailo Dokuchaev, Arnaldo Mandel, Makar Plakhotnyk","title":"The cone of quasi-semimetrics and exponent matrices of tiled orders","comments":"14 pages","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.CO","license":"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/","abstract":"  Finite quasi semimetrics on $n$ can be thought of as nonnegative valuations\non the edges of a complete directed graph on $n$ vertices satisfying all\npossible triangle inequalities. They comprise a polyhedral cone whose symmetry\ngroups were studied for small $n$ by Deza, Dutour and Panteleeva. We show that\nthe symmetry and combinatorial symmetry groups are as they conjectured.\nIntegral quasi semimetrics have apecial place in the theory of tiled orders,\nbeing known as exponent matrices, and can be viewed as monoids under\ncomponentwise maximum; we provide a novel derivation of the automorphism group\nof that monoid. Some of these results follow from more general consideration of\npolyhedral cones that are closed under componentwise maximum.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 12 May 2020 00:13:18 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 17 Mar 2021 18:53:39 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 27 Sep 2021 21:49:37 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-09-29"}
{"id":"2005.05493","submitter":"Sanjay Prabhakar","authors":"Sanjay Prabhakar","title":"Error analysis of bit-flip qubits under random telegraph noise for low\n  and high temperature measurement application","comments":"8 pages, 8 figures","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"cond-mat.mes-hall quant-ph","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Achieving small error for qubit gate operations under random telegraph noise\n(RTN) is of great interest for potential applications in quantum computing and\nquantum error correction. I calculate the error generated in the qubit driven\nby $\\pi$, CORPSE, SCORPSE, symmetric and asymmetric pulses in presence of RTN.\nFor a special case when pulse acts in x-direction and RTN in z-direction, I\nfind that for small value of noise correlation time, $\\pi$-pulse has small\nerror among all the other pulses. For large value of noise correlation time,\npossibly white noise, symmetric pulse generates small error for small energy\namplitudes of noise strength, whereas CORPSE pulse has small error for large\nenergy amplitudes of noise strength. For the pulses acting in all the three\ndirections, several pulse sequences were identified that generate small error\nin presence of small and large strength of energy amplitudes of RTN. More\nprecisely, when $\\pi$ pulse acts in x direction, CORPSE pulse acts in y\ndirection and SCORPSE pulse acts in z-direction then such pulse sequences\ninduces small error and may consider for better candidate in implementing of\nbit-flip quantum error correction. Error analysis of small energy amplitudes of\nRTN may be useful for low temperature measurements, whereas error analysis of\nlarge energy amplitudes of RTN may be useful for room temperature measurements\nof quantum error correction codes.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 12 May 2020 00:34:42 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-05-13"}
